[[module CSS]]
@import url('https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--code/theme%3Ascp-human-resources-sigma/1');
[[/module]]

[[include :scp-wiki:component:interwiki-style
| priority=1
| theme=https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--code/theme%3Ascp-human-resources-sigma/1
]]

[[iftags +theme]]
[[>]]
**Rating:**
[[module rate]]
[[/>]]

+ Usage

This is a Sigma-9 theme based on the [[[theme:scp-human-resources|SCP Human Resources Black Highlighter CSS Theme]]], which is itself an extension of the [[[theme:scp-offices-theme|SCP Offices Theme]]].

To import this theme to your page, put the following anywhere inside it:

[[div class="code"]]
@@[[include :scp-wiki:theme:scp-human-resources-sigma]]@@
[[/div]]

Please do not import this theme using the standard CSS @import method. No one can stop you from doing that, but importing the theme using [[include]] adds your page to a list of Backlinks. This is useful for seeing what pages would be affected when this theme is updated, and allows any errors caused by that to be noticed and corrected much faster.

You can view any page's Backlinks by clicking "+ Options" at the bottom of the page, then "Backlinks".

-----

+ Examples

[[include component:image-block name=hrlogo.png|caption=SCP Human Resources Theme|width=200px]]

A horizontal rule can be created with 5 hyphens "-----" and extends across the whole page if it's not placed inside anything (eg a blockquote). The lines separating sections of this document are horizontal rules.

Titles can be created by putting between one and six plus "+" at the start of the line

